---

<BlockLayout
  title="AI stack"
  description={`Best-practices guide to the AI tools PointCast uses — what each is good at, when to reach for them. ${TOOLS.length} tools across ${categories.length} categories.`}
  image="/images/og/ai-stack.png"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  alternates={[{ type: 'application/json', href: '/ai-stack.json', title: 'AI stack (JSON)' }]}
>
  <div class="page">
    <nav class="crumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
      <span>ai-stack</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="hero">
      <p class="kicker">AI STACK · BEST PRACTICES · {TOOLS.length} TOOLS</p>
      <h1 class="display">What we reach for.</h1>
      <p class="dek">
        A hand-curated working list. Not a directory. What each AI tool
        is good at, when to reach for it, when not to. Opinionated —
        this is our stack, not your stack. Take what's useful.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="legend">
      <p class="legend__label mono">USAGE TIER</p>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="tag tag--daily">DAILY</span> — core tool, reached for constantly</li>
        <li><span class="tag tag--weekly">WEEKLY</span> — routine use for specific tasks</li>
        <li><span class="tag tag--occasional">OCCASIONAL</span> — when the job calls for it</li>
        <li><span class="tag tag--watching">WATCHING</span> — tested, not yet adopted</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    {Object.keys(byCategory).map((cat) => (
      <section class="category">
        <header class="category__head">
          <h2 class="category__title">{cat}</h2>
          <p class="category__count mono">{byCategory[cat].length} tools</p>
        </header>
        <div class="tools">
          {byCategory[cat].map((t) => (
            <article class={`tool tool--${t.tier}`}>
              <header class="tool__head">
                <span class={`tag tag--${t.tier}`}>{tierLabel(t.tier)}</span>
                {t.url ? (
                  <h3 class="tool__name"><a href={t.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener">{t.name} ↗</a></h3>
                ) : (
                  <h3 class="tool__name">{t.name}</h3>
                )}
                <span class="tool__maker mono">{t.maker}</span>
              </header>
              <dl class="tool__facts">
                <div>
                  <dt class="mono">GOOD AT</dt>
                  <dd>{t.goodAt}</dd>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <dt class="mono">REACH FOR</dt>
                  <dd>{t.reachFor}</dd>
                </div>
                {t.avoidFor && (
                  <div>
                    <dt class="mono">AVOID FOR</dt>
                    <dd>{t.avoidFor}</dd>
                  </div>
                )}
                {t.mikesTake && (
                  <div>
                    <dt class="mono">MH TAKE</dt>
                    <dd class="tool__take">{t.mikesTake}</dd>
                  </div>
                )}
                {t.pointcastUses && (
                  <div>
                    <dt class="mono">POINTCAST</dt>
                    <dd>{t.pointcastUses}</dd>
                  </div>
                )}
              </dl>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>
    ))}

    <section class="principles">
      <p class="kicker">PRINCIPLES · HOW WE PICK</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Voice fit first.</strong> Claude reads like a colleague. ChatGPT reads like a product. Pick the one whose voice aligns with how you think.</li>
        <li><strong>Use the best model for the job, not the one in the subscription.</strong> Pay for two at once if that's what the work needs. A bad output on the wrong model costs more than the second sub.</li>
        <li><strong>Code needs tool-use, not just completion.</strong> Claude Code over Claude-the-chat for anything spanning files.</li>
        <li><strong>Image aesthetics ≠ image function.</strong> Midjourney for feel, Ideogram for text, Flux for photo.</li>
        <li><strong>Video is in its Sora-moment.</strong> Coherence is moving fast. Experiment quarterly — the leader shifts.</li>
        <li><strong>Agents are a layer, not a product.</strong> Manus for ops, Claude Code for engineering, Codex for review. Different stacks, same workflow.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <aside class="surfaces">
      <p class="kicker">RELATED</p>
      <ul class="surfaces__list">
        <li><a href="/stack"><span class="mono">TECH</span> /stack</a></li>
        <li><a href="/manifesto"><span class="mono">CANON</span> /manifesto</a></li>
        <li><a href="/for-agents"><span class="mono">AGENTS</span> /for-agents</a></li>
        <li><a href="/ai-stack.json"><span class="mono">JSON</span> /ai-stack.json</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BlockLayout>

